                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330103-28-victim376 t18330103-28-viclabel165"></join>, who lives in <placeName id="t18330103-28-crimeloc166">John-court, Marylebone-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18330103-28-crimeloc166" type="placeName" value="John-court, Marylebone-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18330103-28-crimeloc166" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330103-28-off163 t18330103-28-crimeloc166"></join>. On the night of the 6th of December I saw the prisoner, with two others, standing next door to our shop - he left the other two, went to our shop window, put his hand through a square of glass, which I had taken out that day, and took out this pair of shoes; he put them under his pinafore, and went to his companions - he had made more attempts than one to take them; he took them off a nail - I went and took him; his two companions ran away - he asked me to forgive him.</p>
